# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default-deny .gitignore
# Ignore everything, then re-allow ONLY what builds/runs the app.
# Anything new at the root (scratch scripts, notes, AI configs,
# CLAUDE.md, RESUME.txt, .claude/, .gemini/, etc.) is ignored
# automatically — no need to list it.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) Deny every top-level entry...
/*

# 2) ...then re-allow the runtime surface.
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/backend/
!/frontend/

# 3) Inside the allowed dirs, still keep secrets, deps and build output out.
#    (.env.example is intentionally NOT matched by **/.env, so it stays tracked.)
**/.env
**/*.local
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/dev-dist/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/venv/
**/*.duckdb
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite3

# 4) Local-only design/marketing material, ignored wherever it appears.
assets/
social-media/
